<p style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap">Good morning Grant,</p>
<p style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap">Thank you so much for your email and for =
sharing the process document for my claim (C90306048) at 23 Mays Street, De=
vonport. I really appreciate your effort to outline the framework and the c=
hance to work together on this. It=E2=80=99s
 great to see the team involved, and I=E2=80=99d love your guidance on how =
we can move forward smoothly.</p>
<p style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap">I=E2=80=99ve looked over the process map =
and have a few thoughts to ensure we get this right, especially around safe=
ty and planning. I=E2=80=99ve heard from firefighters about significant fir=
e damage and smoke exiting the roof=E2=80=94initially thought
 to originate there by Devonport Flagstaff=E2=80=94which has me concerned a=
bout the house=E2=80=99s condition.</p>
<p style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap">Could we please consider the following ad=
justments?</p>
<ul type=3D"disc">
<li class=3D"x_MsoNormal" style=3D""><strong><span style=3D"font-family:&qu=
ot;Aptos&quot;,sans-serif">Clarify Claim Scope</span></strong>: Is this the=
 plan for both house and contents claims? If so, should it therefore be lin=
ked to both policy numbers to ensure all coverage
 is included?</li><li class=3D"x_MsoNormal" style=3D""><strong><span style=
=3D"font-family:&quot;Aptos&quot;,sans-serif">Prioritize Health &amp; Safet=
y</span></strong>: I=E2=80=99d feel more comfortable if we scheduled indepe=
ndent assessments (electrical, structural, gas, moisture/mould) before any =
major
 work, alongside the July 9 asbestos survey. The master electrician=E2=80=
=99s finding that the property is uninhabitable due to electrical hazards i=
s a key concern.</li><li class=3D"x_MsoNormal" style=3D""><strong><span sty=
le=3D"font-family:&quot;Aptos&quot;,sans-serif">Assessment-Only Focus</span=
></strong>: As previously expressed, could we limit initial tasks to enabli=
ng damage assessment (e.g., securing the site, debris removal) rather
 than repairs (e.g., upstairs decontamination, curtain cleaning)? This woul=
d allow for a thorough evaluation and mutual agreement on remediation. The =
planned upstairs cleaning (July 21-25) feels premature for these reasons:
</li></ul>
<ul type=3D"disc">
<ol start=3D"1" type=3D"1">
<li class=3D"x_MsoNormal" style=3D"">We need to assess damage before repair=
 to preserve evidence.</li><li class=3D"x_MsoNormal" style=3D"">If the gas =
unit (likely damaged) requires removal, the ceiling may need cutting, neces=
sitating re-cleaning.</li><li class=3D"x_MsoNormal" style=3D"">The electric=
ian=E2=80=99s uninhabitable ruling requires electrical work first.</li><li =
class=3D"x_MsoNormal" style=3D"">Firefighters switched off water (possibly =
gas?) and electricity, which must be assessed and remediated.</li><li class=
=3D"x_MsoNormal" style=3D"">With 4 pets and hybrid work, noisy basement/dec=
k/roof work makes living there untenable until completed.</li></ol>
</ul>
<ul type=3D"disc">
<li class=3D"x_MsoNormal" style=3D""><strong><span style=3D"font-family:&qu=
ot;Aptos&quot;,sans-serif">Asbestos Survey Details</span></strong>: While I=
=E2=80=99m supportive of the July 9 survey, could you please share who will=
 conduct it, the scope and tests involved, and how I can
 independently verify the results? Also, can the funding for this be covere=
d under the claim preparation provision?</li><li class=3D"x_MsoNormal" styl=
e=3D""><strong><span style=3D"font-family:&quot;Aptos&quot;,sans-serif">Str=
uctural Engineer Guidelines</span></strong>: I previously asked about guide=
lines for paying a structural engineer, as per the provision for claim prep=
aration. Could you
 please provide these, as I believe an independent assessment should preced=
e any repair work?</li></ul>
<p style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap">I=E2=80=99d be grateful if you could prov=
ide a revised plan with a written timeline for expert sign-offs and re-occu=
pation only after safety is assured, preferably via email, by July 15, 2025=
. I=E2=80=99m really looking forward to working with
 you for a safe and fair outcome.</p>
<p style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap">Kind regards,</p>
<p style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap">Raffaella del Prete</p>
<p style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap">&nbsp;</p>
<div>
<blockquote style=3D"margin-top:5.0pt; margin-bottom:5.0pt">
<div>
<p class=3D"x_MsoNormal">On 7 Jul 2025, at 5:31<span style=3D"font-family:&=
quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif">=E2=80=AF</span>PM, Grant Metson &lt;<a href=
